Sentencas: The compatibility of La(0.9)Sr(0.1)Ga(0.8)Mg(0.2)O(2.85) perovskite oxide as an electrolyte for solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs) was (i)nvestigated.
Titulo: Compatibility of La0.9Sr0.1Ga0.8Mg0.2O2.85 as the electrolyte for SOFCs

Sentencas: After single SOFC tests using Pt as cathode and anode, the surface morphologies of La(0.9)Sr(0.1)Ga(0.8)Mg(0.2)O(2.85) were changed.
Titulo: Compatibility of La0.9Sr0.1Ga0.8Mg0.2O2.85 as the electrolyte for SOFCs

Sentencas: For the cathode side, second phases were formed along grain boundaries, but there was no significant change on the surface of grains.
Titulo: Compatibility of La0.9Sr0.1Ga0.8Mg0.2O2.85 as the electrolyte for SOFCs

Sentencas: As for the anode side, two significant compositional changes were found by SIMS.
Titulo: Compatibility of La0.9Sr0.1Ga0.8Mg0.2O2.85 as the electrolyte for SOFCs

Sentencas: The first is that La(0.9)Sr(0.1)Ga(0.8)Mg(0.2)O(2.85) reacted with other components such as alumina tubes or Pyrex glass sealant in the test cell.
Titulo: Compatibility of La0.9Sr0.1Ga0.8Mg0.2O2.85 as the electrolyte for SOFCs

Sentencas: The second is a significant depletion of B-site ions, especially Ga ion, from the surface outside the effective electrode area in La(0.9)Sr(0.1)Ga(0.8)Mg(0.2)O(2.85), and the surface morphology was changed from dense to porous.
Titulo: Compatibility of La0.9Sr0.1Ga0.8Mg0.2O2.85 as the electrolyte for SOFCs

Sentencas: Because Ga monovalent compounds, such as Ga(2)O, have high vapor pressures in the reducing atmosphere around p(O(2)) = 10(-24) atm, the Ga depletion can be ascribed to the vaporization of the Ga component.
Titulo: Compatibility of La0.9Sr0.1Ga0.8Mg0.2O2.85 as the electrolyte for SOFCs
